### What's now live
The wire-level optimisations from 2026-05-08 are running in the dev
sandbox:
- `execute_query_iter` streaming reads on the SQL Warehouse path.
- `compute_diff_materialized` CTAS-based incremental diffs (diff rows
  stay in Databricks until the build streams them into Ladybug).
- `bulk_insert_iter` + `iter_triples` on the LadybugDB flat store.
- Viewport-required `/dtwin/sync/load` (default 50k limit, 500k hard
  cap from `DTWIN_MAX_VIZ_TRIPLES`).
- TaskManager result trimming (1 MiB threshold from
  `TASK_RESULT_INLINE_BYTES`, head 200 from
  `TASK_RESULT_LIST_HEAD`).
- Soft warning over 100k rows on `execute_query` from
  `DATABRICKS_MAX_FETCHALL_ROWS`.
- Graph-mode SHACL DQ caps at 2M triples
  (`DTWIN_MAX_GRAPH_DQ_TRIPLES`).

All defaults are set inside the code and rendered through
`app.yaml.template` only when explicitly overridden — production-style
tuning is therefore a one-line change in `scripts/deploy.config.sh` +
template, no code edit required.

