## Streaming-build progress visible in the application logs

### Context
The build page already showed live progression (rows written / total)
because the build pipeline pushes `update_progress` calls through the
TaskManager. The same information was *not* in the application log,
so anyone tailing pod logs (Databricks Apps → Logs panel) had to wait
for the post-phase summary line and could not tell if a long-running
full rebuild was still making forward progress mid-flight.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py`
   - New `_make_progress_logger(phase, ui_callback)` helper. Wraps the
     existing UI progress closure and adds a throttled
     `logger.info(...)` line every
     `_BuildPipeline._LOG_PROGRESS_EVERY_ROWS` rows (default 50 000)
     plus one final line on the last batch. Format is
     `[DT-BUILD <task_id>] <phase>: <done>/<total> triples (<pct>%)`.
   - `_apply_full_rebuild` and `_apply_incremental_changes` now build
     their on_progress via the helper. The original UI callbacks are
     renamed `_on_ui_progress_full` / `_on_ui_del_progress` /
     `_on_ui_add_progress` and remain the inner delegate, so the
     build page keeps updating exactly as before.
   - In API mode (`build_kind="api"`) the inner UI callback is `None`
     (TaskManager updates were already suppressed there), but the
     log line still fires — so even API-driven builds now print
     progress to the pod log.

2. `src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py`
   - New module-level `_make_scheduled_progress_logger(domain_name,
     phase)` mirroring the pipeline helper, throttled by
     `_SCHEDULED_LOG_PROGRESS_EVERY_ROWS` (50 000).
   - `_stream_full_into_store` and `_stream_diff_into_store` gained
     two optional kwargs (`domain_name`, `expected_total`) — both
     default to empty/zero so external call sites are unaffected. When
     `domain_name` is set, the scheduled-build progress logger is
     wired into `bulk_insert_iter` (Ladybug streaming COPY FROM) and
     the row-by-row fallback. Format is
     `Scheduled build [<domain>]: <phase> <done>/<total> triples (<pct>%)`.
   - `_write_graph_triples` now counts the VIEW upfront for the full
     rebuild path so the percentage in scheduled-build logs is
     meaningful, and it logs a "streaming N triples (batch_size=…)"
     opener on each phase to match the build page wording.

### Sample log output (full rebuild on a 1.2M-triple domain)
```
[DT-BUILD 7e5f…] full rebuild: 50000/1234567 triples (4.0%)
[DT-BUILD 7e5f…] full rebuild: 100000/1234567 triples (8.1%)
[DT-BUILD 7e5f…] full rebuild: 150000/1234567 triples (12.1%)
…
[DT-BUILD 7e5f…] full rebuild: 1234567/1234567 triples (100.0%)
[DT-BUILD 7e5f…] streamed 1234567 triples into <graph>
```

### Modified files
- src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py
- src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py
- changelogs/v0.3.0/2026-05-09.log

