## Stop building Sphinx in CI — keep scripts for manual builds

Context: The Sphinx HTML site was being rebuilt on every CI push and the
283 generated artifacts under `docs/sphinx/_build/` were being committed
to the repo, where they routinely went stale between regenerations. We
keep the build tooling (sources, `scripts/build_docs.sh`, `docs/sphinx/Makefile`,
`docs/sphinx/conf.py`) so anyone who wants the rendered API HTML can
still produce it locally — we just stop forcing it on every change.

Changes:

1. .github/workflows/ci.yml
   Remove the `docs:` job (no more `make html` in CI).
2. .gitignore
   Add `docs/sphinx/_build/` so future local builds stay out of the repo.
3. .cursor/08-testing-and-deployment.mdc
   Sphinx §: re-build step is now optional; .rst sources still tracked.
4. .claude/skills/changelog/SKILL.md
   Step 6 — keep .rst updates, drop the build requirement.
5. .claude/skills/adding-subpackage/SKILL.md
   Step 4 — `.rst` page still required, `scripts/build_docs.sh` is optional.
   "Don't" list — drop the obsolete "make docs warnings will fail review".
6. .claude/skills/code-review/SKILL.md
   Documentation step — clarify that Sphinx HTML is local-only.
7. docs/README.md
   Generated API Docs § — clarify that the site is built locally on demand
   and is no longer built or published by CI.
8. docs/code_organization.md
   §11.2 — re-build step is now optional; flagged that artifacts are
   gitignored.
9. docs/graphdb-integration.md
   Step 9 — note that `docs/sphinx/api/<pkg>.rst` is required but the
   HTML build is local on demand.
10. git rm -r docs/sphinx/_build/
    Untrack the 283 stale build artifacts. They will regenerate locally
    via `scripts/build_docs.sh` whenever a contributor wants the site.

