## Knowledge graph search respects Lakebase when global config defaults to Ladybug

Context: Sigma graph search uses ``POST /dtwin/sync/filter`` → ``get_triplestore(..., backend="graph")``.
When ``GlobalConfigService.load`` returns the empty template (``graph_engine: ladybug``) while the
domain session still mirrors ``lakebase`` under ``domain.settings.registry`` (after Settings → Graph DB),
the factory previously passed ``engine=None`` or ``ladybug`` into ``GraphDBFactory``, so preview/expand
could hit LadybugDB instead of Postgres. GraphQL domain load also synced Ladybug archives even when
Lakebase was selected.

Changes:

1. ``src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreFactory.py``
   Read ``graph_engine`` / ``graph_engine_config`` from the domain registry mirror; when the mirror
   is ``lakebase`` but global resolution is not, prefer Lakebase and merge engine config (global keys
   win on overlap). Coalesce ``engine=None`` to ``ladybug`` only after mirror/global resolution.
2. ``src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py``
   Skip Ladybug volume sync when ``DigitalTwin.resolve_graph_engine`` is ``lakebase``.
3. ``tests/test_triplestore_factory.py``
   Regression test for mirror overriding global ``ladybug``.

